The paper focuses on the process of process modeling, which is a key aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). The study also examines how modeling behavior affects the resulting process model, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of metrics to test the conjectures suggests a data-driven approach, which is common in database research (cs.DB). The study also touches on the ease of understanding the resulting process model, which is relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and social informatics (cs.SI).
